cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software, please cite it as below."
title: "AnalisisCuant"
abstract: >-
  A 100% browser-based quantitative statistics tool for academic and
  institutional research. Runs entirely client-side (no backend, no
  install): descriptive statistics, normality testing, Pearson
  correlation, Student's t-test, one-way ANOVA, Likert scale reliability
  (Cronbach's alpha), and simple linear regression, with self-contained
  HTML/TXT report export in Spanish and English.
authors:
